l%20Salam%20Arif%2C%20the%20second%20President%20of%20Iraq%2C%20played%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20the%201958%20revolution%20that%20overthrew%20the%20monarchy.%20On%20April%2013%2C%201966%2C%20Arif%20died%20when%20his%20Iraqi%20Air%20Force%20plane%2C%20a%20de%20Havilland%20DH.104%20Dove%2C%20crashed%20near%20Basra.%20His%20brother%2C%20Abdul%20Rahman%20Arif%2C%20succeeded%20him%20as%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Humberto%20de%20Alencar%20Castelo%20Branco%2C%20President%20of%20Brazil%20(1967)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHumberto%20de%20Alencar%20Castelo%20Branco%2C%20the%2026th%20President%20of%20Brazil%20and%20a%20key%20figure%20in%20the%20former%20military%20dictatorship%2C%20died%20on%20July%2018%2C%201967.%20Shortly%20after%20his%20presidency%20ended%2C%20Castelo%20Branco's%20Piper%20PA-23%20Aztec%20collided%20mid-air%20with%20a%20Brazilian%20Air%20Force%20Lockheed%20T-33%2C%20leading%20to%20his%20death.%20His%20passing%20was%20shrouded%20in%20controversy%20and%20conspiracy%20theories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E6.%20Sanjay%20Gandhi%2C%20Indian%20politician%20and%20Congress%20leader%20(1980)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESanjay%20Gandhi%2C%20son%20of%20former%20prime%20minister%20Indira%20Gandhi%2C%20died%20on%20June%2023%2C%201980.%20Sanjay's%20life%20was%20cut%20short%20when%20he%20lost%20control%20of%20his%20aircraft%20at%20Delhi's%20Safdarjung%20airport.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E7.%20Rashid%20Karami%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20of%20Lebanon%20(1987)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERashid%20Karami%2C%20Lebanon's%20most%20frequently%20elected%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20was%20a%20prominent%20figure%20during%20the%20Lebanese%20Civil%20War.%20On%20June%201%2C%201987%2C%20a%20bomb%20exploded%20in%20his%20helicopter%20en%20route%20to%20Beirut%2C%20killing%20Karami%20and%20wounding%20several%20others%20on%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E8.%20Muhammad%20Zia-ul-Haq%2C%20President%20of%20Pakistan%20(1988)%3C%2Fstron